name: $resourceType
desc: Returns the FHIR type name for this instance

name: $contentType
desc: Returns: Identifies the type of the data in the attachment and allows a method to be chosen to interpret or render the data. Includes mime type parameters such as charset where appropriate.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: Identifies the type of the data in the attachment and allows a method to be chosen to interpret or render the data. Includes mime type parameters such as charset where appropriate.

name: $language
desc: Returns: The human language of the content. The value can be any valid value according to BCP 47.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: The human language of the content. The value can be any valid value according to BCP 47.

name: $data
desc: Returns: The actual data of the attachment - a sequence of bytes, base64 encoded.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: The actual data of the attachment - a sequence of bytes, base64 encoded.

name: $url
desc: Returns: A location where the data can be accessed.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: A location where the data can be accessed.

name: $size
desc: Returns: The number of bytes of data that make up this attachment (before base64 encoding, if that is done).

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: The number of bytes of data that make up this attachment (before base64 encoding, if that is done).

name: $hash
desc: Returns: The calculated hash of the data using SHA-1. Represented using base64.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: The calculated hash of the data using SHA-1. Represented using base64.

name: $title
desc: Returns: A label or set of text to display in place of the data.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: A label or set of text to display in place of the data.

name: $creation
desc: Returns: The date that the attachment was first created.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: The date that the attachment was first created.

name: $height
desc: Returns: Height of the image in pixels (photo/video).

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: Height of the image in pixels (photo/video).

name: $width
desc: Returns: Width of the image in pixels (photo/video).

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: Width of the image in pixels (photo/video).

name: $frames
desc: Returns: The number of frames in a photo. This is used with a multi-page fax, or an imaging acquisition context that takes multiple slices in a single image, or an animated gif. If there is more than one frame, this SHALL have a value in order to alert interface software that a multi-frame capable rendering widget is required.

name: $duration
desc: Returns: The duration of the recording in seconds - for audio and video.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: The duration of the recording in seconds - for audio and video.

name: $pages
desc: Returns: The number of pages when printed.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: The number of pages when printed.
